@page "/privacy"

<PageContainer MaxWidth="default">
    <div class="space-y-8">
        <header class="space-y-2">
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="pt-6 text-slate-600">
                CSV Checker is designed for <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-900">local, ephemeral diagnostics</strong>.
                We do <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-900">not</strong> store, share, or sell your uploaded data.
            </p>
        </header>

        <section class="space-y-3">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">File processing</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700">
                <li>Uploaded CSV files are processed <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-900">in memory only</strong> to generate a diagnostic report.</li>
                <li>Files are <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-900">never written to disk</strong> and are discarded immediately after processing.</li>
                <li>We do not retain copies of uploaded files or their contents.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Reports</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700">
                <li>Diagnostic reports are generated on demand and accessed via a temporary report token.</li>
                <li>Reports are <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-900">not permanently stored</strong> and automatically expire after <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-900">1 hour</strong>.</li>
                <li>Once expired, reports and associated metadata are no longer accessible.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Analytics &amp; telemetry</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700">
                <li>
                    We use Google Analytics to collect <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-900">anonymous usage statistics</strong>
                    (such as page views and feature usage).
                </li>
                <li>
                    CSV contents, row data, and field values are <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-900">never</strong> sent to analytics services.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Operational telemetry is limited to non-content metrics
                    (for example: file size, row count, and error counts) to improve reliability and performance.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Data sharing</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700">
                <li>We do not sell or share user data.</li>
                <li>Uploaded files and report contents are never used for training, profiling, or marketing.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <p class="text-slate-600">
            If you have questions or concerns about how data is handled,
            please <a class="text-teal-700 underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-teal-800" href="/contact">contact us</a>.
        </p>
    </div>
</PageContainer>
